## Architecture

- `src/{{ package_name }}/` — main package (src-layout)
- `tests/` — pytest tests; shared fixtures in `conftest.py`
{% if use_api -%}
- `src/{{ package_name }}/api/` — FastAPI app and route handlers
{% endif -%}
{% if use_db -%}
- `src/{{ package_name }}/db/` — SQLAlchemy models and session factory
- `alembic/` — database migrations (auto-generated, not hand-edited)
{% endif -%}
{% if use_cli -%}
- `src/{{ package_name }}/cli.py` — Typer CLI entrypoint
{% endif -%}
{% if use_iot -%}
- `src/{{ package_name }}/drivers/` — hardware drivers (serial, GPIO, MQTT)
- `config/` — device configuration (not committed — copy from `config/device.yaml.example`)
{% endif -%}
{% if use_ml -%}
- `notebooks/` — Jupyter notebooks for exploration
- `data/` — datasets (not committed; use DVC if `init_dvc=true`)
{% endif %}

## Conventions

- All code must pass `mypy --strict`{% if not use_typecheck %} (disabled in this project — enable by adding `use_typecheck=true`){% endif %}
- Format and lint: ruff (line length 88, Python 3.11+)
- Tests: pytest, fixtures in `conftest.py`
- Commits: Conventional Commits — `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`, etc.
- PRs: squash-merge to main, delete branch after merge
{% if use_db -%}
- Always create migrations with `just make-migration` — never hand-edit `alembic/versions/`
- SQL: use SQLAlchemy ORM or `text()` with bound parameters — no string interpolation
{% endif -%}
{% if use_api -%}
- All new routes go in `src/{{ package_name }}/api/routes/`
- `GET /health` must always return 200 — do not break this endpoint
{% endif %}
